tag.description: Stump of a giant 300 year old tree. It's twin fell during Hugo in 1989.
Historic tree, originally part of the formal gardens. It is listed as a treasure tree.
Local treasure tree located at Historic Rosedale, near the front gate.
Large old tree, on the North Carolina register of big trees. Located near the kitchen of the old plantation.
Many of these boxwoods date to 1815, all others were propagated from the originals in the early 1900's by one of the last owners of the home.
Tresure tree, planted in 1894. Native to coastal "swampy" areas.
One of Rosedale's many treasure trees. It is believed this tree once lined the street that led to the slave quarters.
